### Ticket Flow API
### Use with REST Client (VS Code / Cursor) or IntelliJ HTTP Client
### Docs: GET {{baseUrl}}/docs

@baseUrl = http://localhost:3000

### ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
### Users
### ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

### Create user
# @name createUser
POST {{baseUrl}}/users
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "João Silva",
  "email": "joao.silva@example.com"
}

###

@userId = {{createUser.response.body.id}}

### List all users
GET {{baseUrl}}/users

###

### Get user by id
GET {{baseUrl}}/users/{{userId}}

###

### Update user (name and/or email — at least one field)
PUT {{baseUrl}}/users/{{userId}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "João Silva Atualizado",
  "email": "joao.atualizado@example.com"
}

###

### Delete user (409 if user has tickets)
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/users/{{userId}}

###

### ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
### Tickets
### POST /tickets has rate limit (see TICKET_CREATE_RATE_LIMIT_* in .env)
### ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

### Create ticket (requires existing userId)
# @name createTicket
POST {{baseUrl}}/tickets
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "userId": "{{userId}}",
  "message": "Não consigo acessar minha conta."
}

###

@ticketId = {{createTicket.response.body.id}}

### List all tickets
GET {{baseUrl}}/tickets

###

### Get ticket by id
GET {{baseUrl}}/tickets/{{ticketId}}

###

### Get tickets by user id
GET {{baseUrl}}/tickets/user/{{userId}}

###

### Update ticket status
# Valid status: open | closed | in_progress
PUT {{baseUrl}}/tickets/{{ticketId}}/status
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "status": "in_progress"
}

###

### ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
### Error examples
### ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

### 404 — user not found
GET {{baseUrl}}/users/00000000-0000-4000-8000-000000000000

###

### 404 — create ticket with non-existent user
POST {{baseUrl}}/tickets
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "userId": "00000000-0000-4000-8000-000000000000",
  "message": "Mensagem de teste"
}

###

### 400 — invalid email on create user
POST {{baseUrl}}/users
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Test User",
  "email": "email-invalido"
}

###

### 409 — delete user with associated tickets
# 1) Create user and ticket first (run createUser + createTicket above)
# 2) Then call:
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/users/{{userId}}

###

### 429 — rate limit exceeded on POST /tickets
# Send more requests than TICKET_CREATE_RATE_LIMIT_MAX within the window
POST {{baseUrl}}/tickets
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "userId": "{{userId}}",
  "message": "Requisição extra para testar rate limit"
}
